HOW TO PREPARE FOR STUDYING ABROAD

//
_ london
_ 9 months (8 - 4)

// Vocabulary
1. Application (n) /ˌæplɪˈkeɪʃn/: an ​official ​request for something
2. Requirement (n) /rɪˈkwaɪərmənt/: something that you must do, or something you need
3. Insurance (n) /ɪnˈʃʊrəns/:  an ​agreement in which you ​pay a ​company ​money and they ​pay ​your ​costs if you have an ​accident
4. Arrange (v) /əˈreɪndʒ/:  to ​plan, ​prepare for, or ​organize something
5. Financial (adj) /fəˈnænʃl/
6. Scholarship (n) /ˈskɑːlərʃɪp/:  an ​amount of ​money given by a ​school, ​college, ​university, or other ​organization to ​pay for the ​studies of a ​person with ​great ​ability but little ​money

# idoms
Take up (phrasal verb): to learn or start to do something, especially for pleasure.
Make a plan (collocation): to think of something you can do to solve a problem or make something happen.
